snippet.textDisplay:
Good morning Miranda,
it is 3 a.m. in the morning California time, and I am doing the graveyard shift for the San Bernardino county in Apple Valley California as a professional security officer. I just had to call my daddy out to where I was at a few minutes ago. Because I just found out that my battery went dead as a door nail. :-( Definitely not what I needed right now or financially! But at least I do have my health, for that I am grateful to God for! And while I was sitting here in my car waiting to finish off my shift ... at 6:00am. I just so happened to bump into your song on YouTube, and I really loved it! It's so what I needed to hear right now because of my hardship and situation. It's 48 degrees here in California and it's raining non stop. I have to say Miranda, sometimes we get so caught up in what's wrong, that we overlooked what's right in our lives. So thank you for reminding of that! I just wanted to drop you a line and thank you very much Miranda for all the great songs that you've written and sang to us fans all over the world!
God bless you and yours!
With warmest regards,
Callie Nash from Apple Valley California. 🙂👐👌👍💓
